A sorting algorithm is called stable if the order of equal elements remains the same after sorting.
This means if two elements have the same value, the one that appears first in the original array will also appear first after sorting.

Stable Sorting Algorithms:Merge Sort Insertion Sort,Bubble Sort

Unstable Sorting Algorithms:Quick Sort,Selection Sort,Heap Sort
Example:
Array: (3,a), (1,b), (3,c), (2,d)

After sorting based on the first value:

Stable :
(1,b), (2,d), (3,a), (3,c)

Unstable :
(1,b), (2,d), (3,c), (3,a)

In the stable result, the order of elements with value 3 is preserved.
Stability is useful when sorting objects like students by marks while keeping their roll number order unchanged.